# Code Walkthrough

Every file in the project gets a plain-English walkthrough at the top explaining what's in it. Tone: per `workflow.mdc`.

## Format

- Block comment at the top of every file (after imports).
- Walks through the file in order of the code.
- Says what each function/class/section does.

## Example

```
# === What's in this file ===
# This handles the invoice report calculations.
#
# load_invoice_data()     -- Pulls raw invoice lines from D365 for a date range
# apply_discounts()       -- Applies volume and customer-specific discounts to each line
# calculate_totals()      -- Sums up the discounted lines into a final invoice total
# format_for_excel()      -- Shapes the data into the column layout the Excel export expects
# generate_report()       -- Orchestrates the full pipeline: load -> discount -> total -> format
```

## Rules

- Updated whenever functions are added, removed, or renamed.
- Stale walkthroughs are worse than no walkthrough -- keep them in sync.
- For frontend pages/components: describe what the user sees and what interactions are available.
